OK.

00:46:25.530 --> 00:46:27.324
[LAUGHTER]

00:46:27.930 --> 00:46:28.430
No.

00:46:28.430 --> 00:46:33.210
I don't have a full
answer on that.

00:46:33.210 --> 00:46:37.110
I'm a little concerned that
a lot of the tech companies

00:46:37.110 --> 00:46:42.400
found what I'd say is the area
that they're really great at,

00:46:42.400 --> 00:46:46.620
and that then they stopped
competing in other areas.

00:46:46.620 --> 00:46:48.690
And then the other
companies stopped competing.

00:46:48.690 --> 00:46:50.820
So I'm a little concerned
that everybody is really

00:46:50.820 --> 00:46:53.940
doing incredibly
well in their lane,

00:46:53.940 --> 00:46:56.130
but they're not facing,
at a certain point,

00:46:56.130 --> 00:46:59.250
as much competition, and
that then that may slow down

00:46:59.250 --> 00:47:00.690
some of the innovation.

00:47:00.690 --> 00:47:03.180
And then I'm concerned
on the advertising side

00:47:03.180 --> 00:47:05.010
that between Facebook
and Google it's

00:47:05.010 --> 00:47:07.770
a huge part of the
advertising network.

00:47:07.770 --> 00:47:11.850
And the more Facebook can
close off its network,

00:47:11.850 --> 00:47:14.700
the more actual power it
has against advertisers,

00:47:14.700 --> 00:47:18.360
the opposite of what
people in Congress realize.

00:47:18.360 --> 00:47:22.470
So I think we're going to
need some kind of task force

00:47:22.470 --> 00:47:23.070
to say--

00:47:25.750 --> 00:47:31.050
look, as you can see from
the questions of Zuckerberg,

00:47:31.050 --> 00:47:32.730
not a lot of people
in Congress are

00:47:32.730 --> 00:47:35.792
up to speed to really kind
of figure out what to do.

00:47:35.792 --> 00:47:38.250
I think we're going to need
some kind of commission or task

00:47:38.250 --> 00:47:44.790
force to really study
antitrust, privacy, AI, ethics,

00:47:44.790 --> 00:47:46.920
and come back with some
serious recommendations.

00:47:46.920 --> 00:47:50.730
Because till now, frankly, we
haven't had anything like that.

00:47:50.730 --> 00:47:53.820
Because everything
developed just so quickly

00:47:53.820 --> 00:47:56.040
that we got all
the benefits first.

00:47:56.040 --> 00:48:00.150
And after all the benefits
start to come a few problems.

00:48:00.150 --> 00:48:02.660
Not enough that I
would halt the train,

00:48:02.660 --> 00:48:05.280
but enough that I would really
have a national commission

00:48:05.280 --> 00:48:09.249
to come back with some
thoughtful ideas on this.

00:48:09.249 --> 00:48:11.790
AUDIENCE: I was wondering if
you could talk a little bit more

00:48:11.790 --> 00:48:14.640
about how a microtrend
becomes something bigger

00:48:14.640 --> 00:48:17.400
and like a full national
trend, for example.

